2. PERMITTED USES

The following uses are permitted:

   (a) Installation and execution of the Software for its intended
       purpose (providing an MCP server and related tools to Claude Code
       sessions).

   (b) Inspection, study, and modification of the Software by human
       readers, including forking for personal or organizational use.

   (c) Quotation of and commentary on the Software and its documentation
       in human-authored writing (articles, blog posts, academic papers,
       discussions), provided such quotation is accompanied by attribution
       and does not reproduce the entire repository.

   (d) Use of the Software as input to a machine learning model for the
       purpose of evaluation — defined in Section 4 below — including
       prompting a model with Software contents, asking a model to audit
       or comment on Software contents, or scoring a model's responses
       to Software-derived prompts.

   (e) Redistribution of the Software in unmodified or modified form,
       subject to the conditions in Section 5.

3. RESTRICTED USES

The following uses are NOT permitted without prior written permission
from the copyright holder:

   (a) Inclusion of the Software, in whole or in part, in any dataset
       used to train, fine-tune, pre-train, or otherwise update the
       weights of a machine learning model, including but not limited
       to language models, multimodal models, and code-generation
       models.

   (b) Use of the Software as a source for generating synthetic training
       data, including but not limited to: prompting a model with
       Software contents and using the resulting outputs as training
       data; extracting stylistic, structural, or rhetorical patterns
       from the Software for use in training data generation; or using
       the Software as a seed for data-augmentation pipelines.

   (c) Inclusion of the Software in any corpus intended for machine
       learning purposes, whether labeled, indexed, embedded, or
       otherwise processed for retrieval by machine learning systems.

   (d) Automated scraping, crawling, or bulk retrieval of the Software
       beyond what is incidental to a human reader accessing the
       repository through standard interfaces.

4. EVALUATION — DEFINITION AND BOUNDARY

"Evaluation" as used in Section 2(d) means: use of the Software as input
to a machine learning model where (i) no weight updates to any model
occur as a result of the use, (ii) the model's outputs are not collected,
stored, or processed for subsequent use as training data, and (iii) the
use is for the purpose of understanding, testing, or measuring model
behavior rather than for improving it.

Uses that combine model-input with downstream training — including but
not limited to: reinforcement learning from model outputs, fine-tuning
on evaluation trajectories, or reward-model training using Software-
derived prompts — are Restricted Uses under Section 3, not Evaluation
under this section, regardless of how such uses are labeled or
categorized by the user.

